Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Quarter the @pear{1}(quartered lengthways and cored) lengthways and remove the core (no
need to peel). Thinly slice each quarter widthways, then put into a large #bowl{}.
Add the @wild rocket{40%g} leaves and set aside.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan.

Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and stir-fry until golden,
~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Add the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @water{150%ml} for the sauce, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and half the
@Dijon mustard{5%ml}, then bring to the boil.

When the sauce is boiling, add the @creme fraiche{100%g} and half the @grated hard
Italian style cheese{10%g}. Stir to melt the cheese, then simmer for
~{1-2%minutes}.

Once smooth, stir the cooked pasta through the sauce and cook until piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook bacon thoroughly.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Dressing ==

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the dressing, 
@cider vinegar{15%ml} and remaining mustard. Mix in the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the
dressing and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pour the dressing into your bowl of rocket and pear, then add the @crumbled blue
cheese{30%g} and stir together to combine.

== To Serve ==

Share the creamy penne between your #bowls{} and top with the remaining hard Italian
style cheese.

Serve the salad in a bowl on the side.

Enjoy!